This is my Go To Spot when it comes from Ordering Online all the way to in person. The very rare few times when they may have missed my order, the Team at this location have been quick and very attentive to get the order right. The food is fresh and so is the coffee. However, I would suggest to double check on any new Barista in training as they may tend to get the order wrong by a little, after a few days on their fast paced position they tend to pick up fairly quickly though. If you become a regular, they actually remember your usual order and have it ready before you even pay. There is rarely any waiting inside as the orders are made as quick as they are placed. Although during lunch you may be waiting 5 min or less but thats still not bad. They have a nice seating area outside with plenty of tables both inside and out. The music is always up and great taste in selection. The inside is clean and pleasant. The location of the store sits close to a Whole Foods Store so its great if you in the area to grab and go to Whole Foods.

This was my first time trying this location and it was not the best. I was kindly greeted by Dionte and Stephanie in the usual Starbucks manner I ordered my coffee and bagel double toasted per usual. My drink came out in a satisfactory time and made to perfection but once it was time for me to receive my bagel it was not to my liken. I politely ask Ashley if she can toast my bagel even though I already asked for it to be double toasted. Instead of trying to make the situation right she wanted to be passive aggressive and ask if I wanted to toast it three more time. I responded by letting her know I would just like the inside of my bagel toasted and she continue to be condescending in her tone about toasting the bagel 3 times. She then placed my bagel down and grabbed the wrong bagel even after I told her that was the wrong bagel she completely ignored me and walked away. Stephanie then came over to make the situation right but I nicely told her that was the wrong bagel. I seen that she was a little overwhelmed so I tried to reassure Stephanie that she was doing everything right by just listening to the customer ; something Ashley was failing to do in that moment. Stephanie then reimbursed me for my entire meal and apologized for the misunderstanding and I received a recovery card. Her and Dionte are the only reason I had a decent experience at this location. I refused to take the refund but she insisted that I take it she really tried her best to make that moment right for me.
